<Content>Great stay at the Luna If you are looking for a budget hotel in London, then the Luna Simone is an absolute gem. It is on Belgrave road in-between Pimlico and Victoria tube stations. The hotel is spotlessly clean from top to bottom and the hosts are very nice people. It is run by a couple of brothers and they are proper Londoners,The room we had was small but adequate and is what you would expect from a London hotel in this price range. The bathroom was exceptionally clean and everything was fine. I was surprised to find that there was a free safe in the room also. Our room was on the top floor and for us, was hard work climbing the many stairs to our room. If you have heavy luggage this may be a problem. My advice would be to book early for a room on one of the lower floors. The hotel was completely full, which speaks volumes. We didn't have a problem getting a table in the breakfast room but a large family may have to wait a few minutes for one of the larger tables. The breakfast was with you in a jiffy. It was very nice and perfectly cooked with lots of toast. Service came with a smile and no waiting for anything. The hotel is on a bus route (No 24) wich stops almost outside the door. This bus runs 24 hours, every 5 minutes before 8pm and every 10 minute after that. It's a fantastic route that takes you past Westminster Abbey, Houses of Parliament, Big Ben, Downing Street and Trafalgar Square which all have stops. The bus carries on to Leicester Square in the heart of the theatre area. Get on the top deck and enjoy the views. We purchased day passes for the underground, around 拢5 each and these tickets are good for the buses also (a fantastic deal).We really enjoyed our stay in London and the Luna Simone made it a perfect break. I would not hesitate in recommending this hotel. We will definatly be staying there again. 
