<Content>Just as expected! After all of the rave reviews on Trip Advisor, my husband and I decided to try Luna  Simone for our trip to London. This truly is a GREAT value in London. (We previously stayed at the Darlington, but their prices have greatly increased.)Instead of paying a huge sum of $$ for the Heathrow Express, we took the National Express bus to Victoria Coach station for only 8 pounds per person (round trip). A 50 minute ride from Heathrow, without any traffic. Very comfortable bus with a bathroom as well. Then from Victoria Coach station, it is about a 10-15 minute walk to Luna  Simone. It's not the easiest hotel to find on a map, but we made it with no problems.The rooms are a sunny yellow, but definitely could have used a coat of paint (lots of black wall scratches from luggage being moved around). We stayed in Room 11 that faced the main road, Belgrave. The windows are not well insulated and the street noise is quite clear, as well as the wind whistling against the window panes. But it's not something a pair of earplugs can't fix. The radiator pumped out a lot of heat, that can be manually adjusted. The bed was quite hard, but after multiple days of sightseeing, a welcome place to relax.The bathroom was small, very clean with fantastic water pressure in the shower for a hotel - both my husband and I were impressed. As the previous reviewer suggested, bring your own toiletries. We were provided only with a couple small bars of soap and two plastic pouches of shampoo. (Don't forget your own washcloths!) Fresh towels provided daily.There are plenty of outlets in the room for plugging in your various electronics, bring your own adaptor. Ladies - the hairdryer is tough to maneuver as you have to hold the switch down the entire time you are drying. As well, if you have thick hair like me, the dryer overheats quite frequently. Bring your own if you can.Breakfast was served in the bright, cheery breakfast room and was quite good. Choice of OJ or corn flake