<Author>London_bird
<Content>Good value..... A need at the last minute to get a room in London for one night  I expected to be parting with at least over 100 pounds for a small box! Anyway the Luna  Simone came up trumps with a single room (shared bath) available the day before. Overall it was clean, pleasant and good value with a few minor problems.The room was very small but room under the bed and in the closet if you had a lot of luggage. The bed (single) was very comfortable with the tv high up on the wall above it making it easy to watch in bed. A small handbasin was useful and there was a hairdryer and tea/coffee making facilities if you needed those. I think there was a safe in the closet. I noticed a fan on the wall above the bed - for the summer. Probably useful as I can imagine the room gets very hot and stuffy. The shared bathroom (shared between 2 rooms I think) was spotless with a toliet and shower. Plenty of hot water and the shower pressure was excellent.Breakfast (in a simple, clean dining room downstairs) was simple but adequate. Choice of cooked breakfast or something else (think it was fruit and yoghurt). It was more than acceptable and not too greasy.Now....the downsidesThe room was located directly next to the other single room (the one I was sharing a bathroom with). It was clearly nothing more than a partition wall between the two. I could hear everything from next door. When I first got into my room I was treated to a very loud mobile phone conversation which was then followed by the tv on such a high volume I couldn't hear my own. I called reception who then called up the occupant - fortunately he seemed quite embarassed (I know because I could hear the conversation!). The tv volume was then nothing more than a background annoyance and other than the slamming of his door (whenever he went out to use the bathroom) which shuddered my room there wasn't much noise at all.The front desk staff could do with being a little more organised. When I turned up (9pm on a Sunday night) the young woman shuffled some papers around and then said there was no reservation for me, that they were full and there was nothing she could do!! I asked her to double check and reminded her that I had actually spoken to her the night before to make the reservation. She found it and said she had been looking at the list for the Simone side rather than the Luna side of the hotel. So, she checked me in gave me my key and off I went tupstairs to my room. Let myself in and was surprised to see a double bed with an ensuite bathroom! A minute later and the phone rings and it is the receptionist telling me she had given me the wrong room on the wrong side of the hotel. Back to reception for a change of keys. No apology just a shrug of the shoulders. I wasn't too impressed though! I assume this was a minor glitch but just gave me the impression of a rather disorganised check in procedure. pleased to report no problems on check out and I was charged the correct amount for my room!Would I stay here again - probably but I wouldn't go for one of the single rooms with shared bath. Not because of the shared bathroom but the lack of a proper wall between the rooms! 
