ht at the pub, it's not a far stumble home.The tube stops close by are Victoria (much larger and in the middle of basically a mall) and Pimlico. Pimlico is closer by a block or two but only has the Victoria line running through it. Victoria Station has the Victoria line as well as District and Circle lines. This was very helpful because just about every good tourist stop is on the district or circle line.To sum up: this hotel is amazing for the very low price, especially when you see how much a flat in the area rents for. It was always clean, the breakfast was very good and the location was dang near perfect. We will never stay at any other hotel in London again. 
