<Content>Great stay, kind wonderful family business - like home My 16 yr old daughter and I just returned from London and Paris. It was our first trip traveling in Euroe without my husband and it was last minute and on a budget. We were a bit nervous. We were delighted to find that Luna  Simone B B is easy to get to - walking distance to Victoria Station, the 24 bus stops at the door (goes to many major attraction and runs all night). We were walking distance from the Tate Modern, Evan Evans tours (great- by the way) the Palace, many wonderful restaurants - all prices. It's in an upscale SW1 neighborhood, but the street has a lot of other reasonable hotels and hostels, so it's good for young people. There were a lot of tours of college students coming as we were going home. The B  B is family owned, passed down to twin brothers, their wives and a son. They are wonderfully friendly kind and obviously like people and enjoy their work. They were helpful, made us feel safe and like we were with family (family we actually like and get along with) When my daughter became ill on Easter they scrambled to help us find an open convenience store to buy necessities. They even stored 2 bags of our stinky laundry when we went to Paris before returning home to their B B. But most importantly was how they reach out to everyone and make them feel welcome and connected.The rooms are remodeled, clean, modern with t.v., nice showers, storage, nice firm beds, coffee and tea makings in the room, wholesome breakfast. It's not the Hilton-- so if you want fancy and super-upscale.. this may not be for you.. but it's the best I have found (3rd trip for me to London) for the size and the money.. and most of all the environment. Personally, I am not looking for the Hilton in Europe- I am looking for a comfortable homey friendly place to wake up and come back to after a hard day touring far from home. The first few nights we were right next to the computer room (free). That worked great for my daughter. On return we were in a bigger lighter room on the second floor with a balcony facing Belgrave (still quiet, but no elevator). So if you are looking for simple, homey convenient location, reasonably priced and family like environment with people who you can actually like and enjoy being with.. this is the place Lisa 
